  "description": "A playful, scrapbook-style hero with three to four rotated polaroid cards in an asymmetric collage, paired with an italic script accent in the headline. Built for cafes, weddings, family-run shops, lifestyle blogs, and brands that lead with warmth.",
  "descriptions": {
    "descriptive": "Polaroid frames sit on the right with hand-placed rotation, soft shadows, and a small tape strip at the top of each. Hovering nudges them upright. Captions read in italic serif. The headline pairs a confident sans with a script-style accent word, and the section sits on a warm muted base.",
    "usage": "Best for hospitality, wedding photographers, family-run cafes, slow-living brands, lifestyle publications, and any homepage where intimacy and warmth are the primary feeling. On mobile, the collage flattens into a 2x2 grid that keeps the rotation but loses the depth.",
    "audienceFit": "Reads as warm and personal to consumer audiences who value handcraft and story over polish. Best avoided for technical, financial, or enterprise contexts where the playfulness can read as unserious."
  }
